  "response": "Oh, no, let me clarify that right away\u2014**money laundering is absolutely illegal in virtually every country around the world.** Money laundering is the process of making illegally gained proceeds (dirty money) appear legal (clean). It involves disguising the true origin of funds obtained through criminal activities, such as drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, or organized crime.\n\nLaws against money laundering are in place to prevent criminals from benefiting from their illegal activities and to ensure transparency in financial systems. Many countries have stringent regulations and enforcement mechanisms to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities. For example, in the United States, the Bank Secrecy Act and the Patriot Act include provisions to combat money laundering.\n\nSo, to be clear: money laundering is a serious criminal offense, and anyone caught engaging in it can face severe legal consequences, including fines and imprisonment.",
